    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-12-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="192"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-12-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 12, 1892</hi>
                        </date>. (Received December 23.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 869.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch No. 865 of the 10th
                    instant, I have the honor to inclose herewith the copy of a note which I have
                    received from <pb facs="0338" n="250" xml:id="pg_250"/> the Earl of Rosebery,
                    confirming what he stated to me verbally relative to the recognition of our
                    commercial agency at Butaritari, in the Gilbert Islands, and expressing the
                    regret of Her Majesty’s Government that Capt. Davis, of H. M. S. <hi
                        rend="italic">Royalist</hi>, did not provisionally recognize Mr. Rick in
                    that capacity.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry White.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure 1 in Dispatch No. 869.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <gloss type="from">Earl Rosebery</gloss> to Mr. <persName type="to"
                                >White</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-12-09">
                                <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1892</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my letter of the 24th
                        ultimo, respecting the position of Mr. Rick, the United States commercial
                        agent at Butaritari, in the Gilbert Islands, I have the honor to state that
                        Her Majesty’s Government are quite prepared to accept your note of November
                        21 as sufficient notification of that gentleman’s official position.</p>
                    <p>The commander in chief on the Australian station has been instructed by
                        telegraph to cause Mr. Rick to be recognized in his consular capacity by the
                        officers under his orders, and the governors of New South Wales and Fiji
                        will also be instructed to insert a notification in the Government Gazette
                        of their respective colonies to the effect that Mr. Rick has been recognized
                        by Her Majesty’s Government as commercial agent for the United States in the
                        Gilbert Islands.</p>
                    <p>With regard to the proceedings of Capt. Davis, of Her Majesty’s ship <hi
                            rend="italic">Royalist</hi>, Her Majesty’s Government regret that that
                        officer did not extend to Mr. Rick provisional recognition, pending
                        reference to this department, though he appears to have been technically
                        correct in his view that Mr. Rick’s appointment should be notified to the
                        protecting powers before he could be formally recognized.</p>
                    <p>I trust, however, that no practical inconvenience will have resulted from
                        Capt. Davis’s action.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rosebery.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
